name: Kuramon
description: Kuramon is an Unidentified Digimon that suddenly appeared on a computer network. A single Digi-Egg was born from the malice of humans abusing computers and the aggression from conflicts unfolding over networks. The Digi-Egg was the amalgamation of humanity's destructive instincts, and the mysterious Digimon born from it is incredibly dangerous. It multiplies within a computer network like a virus, causing minor network failures. Kuramon uses its special move Glare Eye to produce a frothy substance from its giant eye.

name: Choromon
description: A super-small Machine Digimon with red eyes that act as photosensors. Choromon's constant restless movements make it seem very cute, but they're just because of its simple programming making it react to bright light. In dark places, it can't move at all. For reasons unknown, it discharges electricity from the tip of its tail when it's in a good mood. It uses its move Jamming Powder to emit metal particles and temporarily confuse its enemy's AI. It then takes advantage of this temporary confusion to flee.

name: Dodomon
description: A Slime Digimon covered entirely in a tough material called Mithril Hair. Dodomon exhibits an aggressive nature right from birth, and even though its fangs haven't grown in yet, it likes to threaten foes by opening wide and pretending to bite them. Because of this behavior, these Digimon are often taken out by others, making Dodomon quite rare. When an enemy approaches, Dodomon attacks by shooting Little Iron Beads from its mouth.

name: Pabumon
description: This Slime Digimon looks like a mere bit of sea-green froth at first glance, but it's actually a totally autonomous creature with a plethora of expressions. Pabumon's delicate surface means it has practically no defense or prowess in combat. It creates infinite tiny foam clones from the pacifier-like object in its mouth. This ability was originally used to develop computer viruses, but Pabumon's lack of life force made for poor implementation. Life is fleeting for this adorable Digimon baby. It uses Adhesive Bubble Blow to release bubbles from its body to bind enemies, giving Pabumon a chance to escape.

name: Punimon
description: A brand new type of Digimon. Three feelers grow from the top of its gelatinous, red body. Punimon is incapable of fighting, instead relying on Acid Bubbles to threaten enemies.

name: Botamon
description: A newborn Digital Monster. Dark peach fuzz covers the surface of Botamon's slimy body. This new addition to the Digital World can't fight, but it can spout Acid Bubbles from its mouth in an attempt to threaten foes.

name: Poyomon
description: This Digimon baby uses its translucent body to float along the Net Ocean like a jellyfish. Possessing the most primitive structural makeup of any Digimon discovered to date, it garners attention from Digital World anthropologists and Digimon fanatics alike. They hail it as a "missing link," potentially capable of unlocking the mystery behind Digimon generation. To protect itself from foes, Poyomon shoots Acid Bubbles from its mouth.

name: Kapurimon
description: A small, In-Training Digimon wearing a metal helmet. The two horns on the helmet contain antennae that can transmit all sorts of radio waves or sounds. Kapurimon has batlike traits, emitting ultrasonic waves from its mouth and recognizing objects ahead of it from the rebounding waves, instead of relying on its weak eyesight. This allows it to remain active no matter what time of day or night it is. Kapurimon uses its special move Howling Hertz to make its two horns resonate. Anyone hit by this attack has their hearing paralyzed, even large Digimon.

name: Koromon
description: A small Digimon whose body has grown a size bigger, its peach fuzz having fallen off. Koromon can move around vigorously, but combat is still beyond its capabilities. It blows Bubbles from its mouth to intimidate foes.

name: Tanemon
description: A Bulb Digimon with what appears to be a seedling sprouting from its head. Tanemon Digivolved from a Yuramon that landed on the ground after drifting through the air in search of the perfect environment. Extremely skittish, it will use its four legs to quickly dig a hole so it can hide its body at the first sign of a threat. While Tanemon's body is hidden underground, the seedling on its head makes it indistinguishable from a plant, protecting it from harm. That being said, this tactic proves ineffective against herbivorous Digimon.

name: Tsunomon
description: A small Digimon with a single horn on its head, formed by hardening one of Punimon's feelers. Having Digivolved to be more animalistic than Punimon, Tsunomon is covered in soft fur. Filled with a playful spirit, Tsunomon loves to pull pranks, and has yet to develop its instinct for conflict.

name: Tsumemon
description: An In-Training Digimon that Digivolved beyond Kuramon. The tips of its feelers are shaped like talons, increasing its ferocity. Tsumemon corrodes data at frightening speed, causing networks to malfunction. Its movement speed is just as fast, making this Digimon difficult to catch once it's Digivolved to this level. It uses its special move Nail Scratch to rake the enemy with the talons on its feelers.

name: Tokomon
description: A small Digimon with four limbs growing out of the bottom of its body (head?). These limbs, which are highly unusual on an In-Training Digimon, give Tokomon a unique and extremely cute look. However, that cuteness can be deceptive, and anyone who reaches out to pet Tokomon may be in for a surprise as it quickly opens its mouth and bites down with its rows of sharp teeth. Tokomon has an innocent personality, though, and doesn't mean any real harm.

name: Dorimon
description: A Lesser Digimon that can run extremely fast, but only in a straight line. Dorimon hate to be tamed, so many remain feral. Approaching it is dangerous, as it will charge in recklessly for a tackle. Dorimon's pointed ears are tough, acting as horns and inflicting a modicum of damage when it tackles. That being said, it can't turn once it has gained enough speed. Dorimon's special move is Metal Drop, spitting metal beads as it charges toward the enemy.

name: Nyaromon
description: A small Digimon with feline traits. Fickle by nature, Nyaromon has quite catlike behavior. While curious and capricious in equal measure, it has a lonely side as well. Nyaromon uses its special move Fox Tail to whip the enemy with the wiry hairs on its tail. However, not a single foe has ever been seen flinching under this attack.

name: Pagumon
description: A small Digimon that can perform low-altitude flight with the ear-like appendages on its head. Pagumon can use these ears deftly like hands, often pulling down its enemy's eyelids or slapping their rear with them mockingly. Particularly mean-spirited, it can often be seen teasing the likes of Koromon or Tsunomon, chasing them around and around. Pagumon may even spit Poison Bubbles from its mouth to bully other Digimon.

name: Yokomon
description: A Bulb Digimon with a big flower blooming on its head. Yokomon moves by deftly manipulating its root-like tentacles, and is able to float softly through the air, albeit for short distances. A curious creature, its restless movements are delightful to behold. Yokomon tend to live in groups—from dozens to hundreds.

name: Bukamon
description: Despite resembling an aquatic dinosaur infant, this playful Digimon can move as skillfully as a seahorse. Bukamon is quick to flee when others draw near, however. Its skin still isn't fit for the high pressure and low temperature of ocean depths, so it can only spend limited amounts of time submerged in the deep.

name: Motimon
description: A soft-bodied Digimon with highly elastic skin, Motimon uses the protrusions beneath its body to waggle its way around. The name "Motimon" comes from its resemblance to a mochi rice cake when it puffs up its body in excitement. Despite its appearance, Motimon possesses a surprisingly high degree of intelligence, and so is believed to have developed from a computer's dictionary feature. Capable of understanding human language, Motimon can occasionally be seen altering the shape of its body in an effort at communication. Motimon uses its mochi-like Elastic Bubbles to restrict opponents' movement.

name: Wanyamon
description: A Digimon that fuses the data of small pet animals such as cats and dogs. Wanyamon is unexpectedly swift, so caution is warranted to prevent its escape. Even so, it gets quite attached if you fawn over it like a pet. Its special move is Smile Fang, going suddenly from an innocent-looking pose to a surprise chomp attack.

name: Agumon
description: A small, dinosaur-like Reptile Digimon that has developed the ability to walk on two legs. Since it hasn't fully matured, it still lacks strength, but its fierce disposition makes it reckless. Hard, sharp claws grow from its hands and feet, and it makes full use of them in battle. Agumon shows much potential, promising Digivolution into a great and powerful Digimon. Its special move is Pepper Breath, spitting flames at its foes.

name: Kudamon
description: A Holy Beast Digimon that's always wrapped around a holy ammunition cartridge. Kudamon is constantly building up holy power within the earring on its left ear, and the amount it accumulates affects the course of its next Digivolution. Calm and collected by nature, it can assess any situation—even combat—with accuracy, ensuring the advantage in battle. If things ever go south, though, Kudamon enters its cartridge to strengthen its defensive position. Its special move Blinding Ray dazzles the enemy with a glaring flash emitted from its earring.

name: Gomamon
description: A Sea Beast Digimon that can move on land and that's covered in temperature-regulating fur. This short, white fur grows longer and turns brown as Gomamon ages. A busybody and a troublemaker, Gomamon loves to get involved in every situation. The streak of red fur running from its head down its back moves in accordance with its mood, bristling when Gomamon is angry. Its claws are sharp enough to cut through solid ice with ease, and anyone who underestimates Gomamon is in for a rude awakening. Its special move is Marching Fishes, with which Gomamon commands a loyal squad of small fish to attack.

name: Coronamon
description: A Beast Digimon born through the fusion of data obtained by observing the sun. Coronamon has a strong sense of justice and a pure, simple-minded personality. Its special move is Corona Flame, which converts all of the stamina in its body into flame power to shoot a fiery missile at the enemy from its forehead.

name: Zubamon
description: Zubamon is one of the Legend-Arms that can transform its body into a weapon. The fabled Legend-Arms are said to be capable of either saving the world in the hands of an angel, or destroying it in the hands of a devil. Zubamon possesses the data of the Twentiest, and often shouts "I am the Twentiest!" without knowing what that means. It dislikes anything warped or twisted, and is in constant pursuit of its ideal of sharpness. In battle and in jest, it's always trying to look sharp, and days when it succeeds put it in a good mood. Though it has its Twenty Dive attack that involves rushing headlong at an enemy, Zubamon's true strength lies in its weapon form.

name: Solarmon
description: A rare species of mechanical Machine Digimon. Some researchers believe Solarmon to be a mutation of Hagurumon, but the truth of the matter remains a mystery. Because its DigiCore generates heat, its body is hot enough to cause burns. Solarmon uses its special move Shiny Ring to throw heat-emitting gears that scorch the enemy.

name: Terriermon
description: An enigmatic Digimon with a massive horn growing from its head. While Terriermon's composition is enough to deem it a Beast Digimon, the form it takes after Digivolving is still unknown. Rumor has it that it's sometimes born with a twin. Terriermon's extreme cuteness and calm behavior don't give the impression that this Digimon is of the Combat Species. Still, the power it exhibits in battle belies its appearance. It uses its signature move Terrier Tornado to spin both of its ears like a propeller, creating a small tornado.

name: Tentomon
description: The prototypical Insectoid Digimon, Tentomon has a hard carapace but a low level of aggression. Tentomon has one claw on each of its forelegs, and four claws on its middle and hind legs. Its middle legs in particular are highly dexterous, similar to human hands. Though other Insectoid Digimon of Tentomon's Digivolution level are consumed by a strong fighting spirit, Tentomon retains a love and appreciation for nature at this stage. Exhibiting a fondness for relaxation, Tentomon stops to smell flowers and nap in the shade of trees. Even so, it does have the special move Super Shocker, which involves using its wings to shoot out amplified bolts of static electricity.

name: ToyAgumon
description: An unusual Digimon composed of blocks made from a special plastic. ToyAgumon is said to be an imitation of Agumon made by children playing on the Internet. It's extremely cute. Unlike the bold and fearless Agumon, ToyAgumon has a skittish side, and its blocks fly apart when it's startled. Despite this, it has a strong sense of justice that won't allow for any sort of wrongdoing. It also adores children, and loves to spend time interacting with them on the Net. Its special move is Plastic Blaze. with which it shoots out a toy missile shaped like a flame. It's surprisingly powerful.

name: Tapirmon
description: A Digimon that resembles a "baku," a being in Japanese folklore that eats dreams. Believed to have been born from a medical computer that monitors brainwaves, Tapirmon seems to feed on human REM sleep data. In the latest round of research, it was also found to possess the ability to erase nightmares and computer viruses. Since it can also return those nightmares and viruses to a benign state, it's believed to be a Holy Digimon. The Holy Ring it wears on one of its forelegs seems likely related to both its special abilities and Holy nature. Tapirmon's special move is Nightmare Syndrome, which releases all of the nightmares it absorbed at once to terrify its adversaries. This is the same special move as that of the Perfect Digimon, Digitamamon, but how the two might be related remains a mystery.

name: Hyokomon
description: A Baby Bird Digimon Digivolved from samurai-related data. Hyokomon trains tirelessly to master the way of the sword and is also developing a secret technique. When it comes to swordsmanship, it talks the talk, but doesn't quite walk the walk yet. The next Digivolution of Hyokomon will only happen when it breaks out of its shell through endless sword training. Its special move is Downward Cleave, utilizing its wings and leg strength to jump up and swing its sword straight down to split its foe in two.

name: Biyomon
description: A Baby Bird Digimon with arm-like wings. Biyomon can use these to dexterously grip objects, though this limits its ability to fly. It spends most of its time on the ground, but can escape into the air when danger draws near. Since it's similar in flying ability to Patamon, Biyomon sees Patamon as a rival. Biyomon's dream is to one day Digivolve into Birdramon and fly freely through the sky. Its nightmare is becoming Kokatorimon, who can't fly at all. Possessed of an inquisitive mind, it likes to peck at the sprout growing from Tanemon's head. Biyomon's special move is Spiral Twister, an attack of spectral flames.

name: Falcomon
description: A Bird Digimon with more developed wings that allow it to fly. In spite of this, Falcomon seems obsessed with appearing from out of the sky riding a giant kite like a ninja. Its special move is Ninja Blade, which involves firing off cross-shaped throwing stars made from its hardened feathers.

name: Salamon
description: Salamon is a young, Sacred-species Digimon with distinctive floppy ears. Since it's still a child, it isn't able to make full use of its holy powers, and has yet to realize its destiny. As a result, its nature is fundamentally unstable, and it's capable of becoming either good or evil. There will likely come a day, however, when Salamon will awaken to its destiny as one of the Virus Busters. After all, it was born a sacred Digimon. Salamon is also an experimental Digimon created by Digimon researchers, and since it was modeled after a human pet, it looks a great deal like a real animal. Its special move Puppy Howl involves letting out a supersonic screech that can paralyze foes.

name: Bearmon
description: A Beast Digimon resembling a small bear, wearing its trademark backwards cap. Although timid at times, Bearmon gets along well with other Digimon, and even possesses uncommon pluck and stamina. Once a battle starts, it continues to fight no matter how many hits it takes, making for a reliable ally. The ability for melee fighting it possesses is so strong that it needs to wrap its fists with leather belts so it won't injure itself with the destructive power of its punches. With its special move Bear Fist, Bearmon leaps at its opponent's chest to drive home a full-force blow.

name: Penmon
description: A Bird Digimon resembling a penguin found in the computer of an Antarctic base. Since Penmon lives in snow-covered regions, it doesn't do well in the heat. It does quite well with humans, conversely, and will happily waddle along behind them. Penmon's wings have degenerated, so it can't fly or walk very quickly. But when it slides across the ice on its belly, it can reach speeds close to 40 mph. When in the water, Penmon can use its small wings to skillfully swim around. Its special move is Super Slap, where it sneaks up on the enemy to smack their cheeks as hard as it can with both arms.

name: Monodramon
description: A Mini Dragon Digimon incapable of flight, despite the bat-like wings on both arms. Monodramon's personality is rather rough—bordering on brutal, and it gives the impression of a Digimon that enjoys a good scrap. It's often found in the middle of most Digital World brawls, causing even the likes of Ogremon to get fed up with its persistence. Monodramon's special move is Knuckle Beater, charging into the enemy with staggering force before unleashing its powerful claws in a straightforward strike.

name: Ryudamon
description: Because of the antiquated interface on its forehead, this Beast Digimon is presumed to be an experimental "Prototype Digimon" from the time before Digimon were discovered. Ryudamon is covered in Japanese-style armor that boasts high defense, yet its movements are quite nimble, allowing it to jump in and fight at brazenly close range. The more it fights, the more it cultivates combat prowess. Ryudamon possesses gallantry, a samurai spirit and a soul that renders it unafraid of powerful enemy Digimon. The data hidden within the deepest part of its DigiCore during the experiment contains such fierce combat data as warlords and dragons from Japanese mythology, and Ryudamon is thought to possess the potential to grow into a mighty Digimon. Its special move is Iai Blade, with which it leaps up to the opponent to fire an iron blade from its mouth at point-blank range.

name: Lucemon
description: Lucemon is an Angel Digimon resembling a child, said to have descended from on high long ago in the Ancient Digital World. It appeared in a time of chaos, and is said to have ushered in a new era of peace and order. However, due to Lucemon's subsequent rebellion, the world was then plunged into a long, dark age. Despite having the appearance of a child, Lucemon is wiser and more powerful than an Ultimate Digimon. It's said that in the modern era, Lucemon's abilities have been passed down to and divided among the Three Celestials Lucemon's special move is Grand Cross, which fires a collection of ten super-heated spheres of light arranged into the shape of a cross as if they were planets in alignment. This attack is even more destructive than Seraphimon's special move Strike of the Seven Stars.

name: Elecmon
description: A Mammal Digimon with a strong sense of curiosity and a love of mischief that it retained after its Digivolution from Tsunomon. Elecmon fans out its nine tails like a peacock in order to intimidate foes in battle. Its special move is Sparkling Thunder.

name: Gaomon
description: A Beast Digimon thought to be a subspecies of sharp-clawed Gazimon. Gaomon specializes in hit-and-run attacks using agile movements. The gloves on its hands are apparently to protect its claws until they grow in properly. Gaomon uses its powerful legs to spin and unleash its special move Double Backhand.

name: Crabmon
description: A Crustacean Digimon that attached metal data that had been dissolved into the Net Ocean to its body, dramatically increasing its combat capability. Crabmon attacks with the giant blades on its left pincer and the powerful grip of its right pincer. For defense, it relies on its spiny shell to damage attackers, and is utterly self-confident in battle. Crabmon is fully aware of the weak points of its joints and underbelly, and thus rarely leaves them exposed. It enjoys trapping its opponents, and is something of a prankster. Crabmon's special move is Scissors Execution, which launches its sharp left pincer right for its adversary's throat.

name: Gabumon
description: A full-fledged Reptile Digimon, despite being covered in fur. Gabumon is an extremely shy, timid creature who always gathers up data left behind by Garurumon to wear like a pelt. Garurumon's pelt also serves to protect Gabumon, since other Digimon fear the original owner. Gabumon's personality makes a complete about-face when it wears the pelt. Its special move is Blue Blaster.

name: Kamemon
description: An Android Digimon that wears a shell like a computer mouse. Kamemon uses its special move Pointer Arrow to fire an arrow-shaped missile that it guides to strike the enemy.

name: Kokuwamon
description: An extremely rare insect Machine Digimon that was recently discovered. No insect Machine Digimon had been discovered up to that point, and so Kokuwamon's existence wasn't even considered a possibility. Its stun gun-shaped head and arms can discharge 100 megavolts of electricity when it senses danger, so none can approach without caution. Even so, Kokuwamon lacks any aggression, sporting instead an accommodating nature that seeks peace. Kokuwamon obtains nourishment from electricity, and recharges itself with the two limbs on its midsection. Its special move is Mini Scissor Claw, which electrifies its pincers to slice through even the sturdiest of objects.

name: Gotsumon
description: An Ore Digimon with powerful defensive abilities, having armored itself using ore data from its surroundings. As spunky, mischievous and ambitious as any young tough guy, Gotsumon leads around groups of low-generation Digimon as it travels the system. It also has a selfish side,and can be a real handful when angered, rampaging like an erupting volcano. The ore data Gotsumon uses for its armor differs depending on where and how it was generated, giving Gotsumon the potential to Digivolve into a number of different forms. Gotsumon's special move is Rock Fist, which shoots extremely hard rocks from its head.

name: Kotemon
description: A Reptile Digimon that aims to become the greatest swordsman of the Digimon world. Kotemon is a hard worker that silently endeavors to train in unseen areas. It never removes its face protector, so its bare face is a total mystery. Although Kotemon is cowardly and prone to crying, it cares for its friends deeply and has a strong sense of justice, and occasionally even displays a stalwart side. With its special move Hothead, it engulfs its bamboo sword in flames before aiming for the head of its foe.

name: Shoutmon
description: A ferocious Digimon with amazing vigor and extreme aggression. Even so, it's friendly to allies, and those recognized by Shoutmon can establish a deep bond that transcends species. Because passion is the source of its strength, Shoutmon won't abandon a battle no matter how much damage it receives, contributing to its savage reputation.

name: Dracomon
description: Dracomon is a Dragon Digimon of an old bloodline said to trace back to the progenitor of all Dramon-species Digimon. It possesses physical capabilities difficult to even imagine given its small size, with its speed and power ranking among the very best of all Rookie Digimon. Though extremely fierce by nature, it also has a softer side it only shows to those it deems worthy of its trust. Despite having wings, they're not fully developed, so Dracomon is unable to fly. One of its other defining characteristics is its drive to collect "shiny things,"and it has an odd attachment to gems and certain types of metal. If it's particularly fond of some shiny object, it will eat it. Its special move is Baby Breath, which it uses to breathe out a blast of hot air.

name: Dorumon
description: Because of the antiquated interface on its forehead, this Beast Digimon is presumed to be an experimental "Prototype Digimon" from the time before Digimon were discovered. The personality characteristic of the Combat Species is particularly apparent in Dorumon. It has a strong instinct for battle, biting and roaring at anything and everything, though it apparently feels a sense of attachment to something after biting it. The strong life force data of the legendary "dragon" was found to have been hidden in the deepest part of its DigiCore during an experiment, and Dorumon apparently has the potential to grow into a mighty Digimon. Dorumon's special move is Metal Cannon, which fires an iron ball from its mouth.

name: Patamon
description: A Mammal Digimon known for its large ears. Patamon can use these to fly, but since it can only do so at a little over 0.5 mph, its its walking speed is said to be considerably faster. Even so, watching it struggle to fly is an endearing sight, making it very popular (although Patamon itself doesn't appreciate such sentiment). Patamon is extremely obedient and very good about doing what it's told. It can also use its hidden holy power without a Holy Ring—a sign that it's descended from an Ancient species of Digimon. Patamon's special move is Air Shot, taking a deep breath and then releasing a powerful blast of air.

name: Huckmon
description: A Mini Dragon Digimon with a cool white sheen. Unfettered and hating shackles, Huckmon's swashbuckling way of life is likely due to the influence of Gankoomon's DNA. It faces the harsh trials imposed by Gankoomon with composure. Huckmon's lineage gives it a keen sense for battle, and training supervised by the Sistermon siblings makes it more than evenly matched in fights against even Ultimate foes. Huckmon specializes in nimble melee combat, using Fifth Rush to cleave the opponent with its tough claws. It pursues its dream to become a Royal Knight like Gankoomon.

name: Palmon
description: A Vegetation Digimon with a tropical flower growing on its head. Though it Digivolved from Tanemon in a reptilian fashion, it's a rare type of Digimon classified as a Vegetation Digimon based on its appearance and characteristics. During the day, Palmon opens its flower and leaf-like appendages to enable photosynthesis. Its root-like feet are usually buried in the ground absorbing nutrients, but it can also use them to walk. The flower on Palmon's head gives off a sweet scent when it's happy or enjoying itself and a foul stench when it's angry or feels threatened. The latter is so bad it can send even larger Digimon running. Palmon's special move is Poison Ivy, with which it entangles its foe in highly poisonous vines. Anything hit by this attack is paralyzed.

name: Floramon
description: A rare Digimon that, like Palmon, Digivolved in reptilian fashion but is classified as a Vegetation Digimon. The entirety of Floramon's face is shaped like a flower, and it generally uses this petal-like shell like a helmet to protect its head. When no predators are around, or when in a good mood, it will spread open the petals on its head and arms. Floramon sees Palmon as a rival, and has a very high opinion of itself. Its special move is Rain of Pollen, which releases clouds of allergy-inducing pollen from the flowers on its arms. Anyone hit by this attack—even a large Digimon—will be robbed of both their composure and will to fight.

name: Muchomon
description: A flightless Bird Digimon that's the spitting image of Penmon. Raised in tropical lands to the south, Muchomon lives a life of constant cheer. It overflows with passion, dances to a samba beat and loves its vivid, richly-colored pelt. Muchomon's special move is Tropical Beak, pecking the opponent with its colorful beak.

name: Lalamon
description: A Vegetation Digimon resembling a flower bud, Lalamon drifts through the sky by rotating the leaves on its head. Despite its lack of expression, it has a great deal of charm. Its special move Seed Blast shoots hard seeds from its mouth with a surprising degree of accuracy.

name: Lunamon
description: A Mammal Digimon resembling a rabbit, born from the fusion of moon observation data. Its large ears can recognize sounds from any distance. Although timid, Lunamon often gets lonely and easily grows attached to others. It uses its special move Tearing Shot to concentrate power into the antenna on its forehead to shoot a beautiful orb of water at the enemy.

name: Renamon
description: A Beast Man Digimon with the appearance of a golden fox. The relationship Renamon has with humans is directly apparent, and its In-Training form can Digivolve into a Digimon of high intelligence if raised properly. Calm and collected at all times, it trains in order to keep its cool in any situation. Renamon's tall, slender form stands out among Rookie Digimon, and it prefers the speed of its many techniques over power when it comes to fighting the enemy. Its special move Diamond Storm hurls razor-sharp wood chips at the enemy.

name: Lopmon
description: Lopmon is the Rookie Digivolution of one sibling in a pair of extremely rare twin Digimon. Of the two, Terriermon has one horn growing from its head, while Lopmon has three. Their ecosystem is steeped in mystery, and while their composition is enough to deem them Beast Digimon, nothing else is known about them. Terriermon has a laid-back personality, albeit with a lot of energy, while Lopmon has the opposite disposition, being more of a lonely crybaby. Neither seem like Digimon of the Combat Species, but they do show unexpected power in battle. Lopmon's special move Blazing Ice fires a blast of icy bullets.

name: Impmon
description: Impmon is a Rookie Digimon that looks like a devil child. It loves to pull pranks, relishing the thought of watching its victims struggle. Rumor has it that whenever Impmon appears, electrical appliances briefly go haywire, so if your screen ever shakes or freezes, it might be because Impmon is pulling a prank. But as much as Impmon delights in mischief and malice, it's not one to meekly bow down before the strong. It puts on a brave face and stands up to them instead. Deep down, it's actually quite lonely. Impmon's signature move is Summon, which calls forth fire and ice elementals.

name: Otamamon
description: A larval Digimon whose epidermis has yet to solidify due to it living underwater. Otamamon swims through swamps and rivers upstream of the Net Ocean using its large tail, occasionally clambering onto rocks with its developed forelimbs to do vocal exercises. Unlike those of an average organism, its hind legs are almost completely undeveloped, acting as rudders in the stead of its propulsive tail. Unlike other Rookies, this Digimon's future Digivolution seems quite promising, but it's extremely prone to mutation, so caution is warranted when raising it. Otamamon's special move is Lullaby Bubble, which sends opponents into an eternal slumber.

name: Gazimon
description: A Mammal Digimon with huge, sharp claws. Gazimon is bipedal, an unusual trait for Mammal types. The claws on its front limbs may have developed while it used them like arms, causing Gazimon to rely on its hind legs for ambulation. Despite its small stature, this Digimon has an exceedingly wild temperament, and never even attempts to get along with humans. The claws on Gazimon's forelimbs are extremely effective for attacking, but are also surprisingly well-suited to digging holes. Due to its mischievous nature, it enjoys making pitfalls for other Digimon to fall into. Gazimon's special move is Electric Stun Blast, which belches out a poisonous gas.

name: Gizamon
description: A Sea Animal Digimon with fins on its feet with which to paddle through water. Gizamon is more suited to life underwater than on land, using its fins and strong hind legs to swim quickly through aquatic areas. On land, however, it bounces around like a frog. Gizamon acts cowardly on land, but displays a ferocious disposition once back in the water. Its special move is Spiral Edge, which attacks foes with its sharp-edged dorsal fins.

name: Guilmon
description: A Digimon resembling a young dinosaur. Although Guilmon is still a Rookie Digimon, it possesses a carnivore's brutality and the great potential as a fighting species that all Digimon naturally possess. The mark on its abdomen is called a DIgital Hazard, and is inscribed on any Digimon with the ability to cause serious damage to computer data. Still, if used for the sake of peace, this ability could potentially make this Digimon a guardian of the Digital World. Guilmon can use its signature move Rock Breaker to destroy even stone with its rugged front claws.

name: Goblimon
description: A Digimon resembling a troublesome imp that loves mischief. Crafty creatures devoid of courage, Goblimon always move in groups, hiding in the shadows of trees or buildings while waiting in ambush. But if the situation goes south, they scatter in all directions, fleeing at full speed. Their intelligence, on the other hand, is above average for Rookie Digimon. Goblimon's special move is Goblin Strike, which hurls fireballs at Mach speed.

name: Shamamon
description: A Goblimon whose duty it is to hear the will of the gods and convey it to its clan. Shamamon conducts a ritual in which it performs a strange dance, and supposedly hears divine messages once its fervor reaches its peak. Shamamon's clan uses this ritual to foretell matters of import. Shamamon uses its special move Shama Hammer to bonk the enemy on the head with the large club it also uses in its ritual.

name: Syakomon
description: A Digimon shaped like a clam and surrounded by a sturdy shell. Its highly developed shell protects what looks like an In-Training Slime. This deceptive Digimon uses its face to lure enemies in before attacking them. Syakomon also boasts a high defense when its shell is closed, repelling small attacks with ease. Its special move Black Pearl Blast fires jadeite formed in its body at the enemy.

name: SnowGoblimon
description: A Goblimon raised in cold, snowy countries. SnowGoblimon wears a warm hat and vest, so cold places are no problem for it, and the skin on the soles of its feet is thick enough to let it traipse over snow without issue. SnowGoblimon's special move is Snow Goblin Volt, which bats rock-filled snowballs at its foe with all the fervor of a demon.

name: Chuumon
description: A mouse-like Digimon that's always filling Sukamon's head with shady ideas. Chuumon has a solid friendship with Sukamon (although perhaps it's only Chuumon that sees things that way). The relationship started when Chuumon was nearly caught in a network system trap named "Carnivore," only to be rescued by Sukamon, who just happened to be passing by. Fundamentally a coward, Chuumon is unrivaled in its slyness and takes off like a shot at the slightest hint of danger. Its special move Cheese Bomb hurls a cheese-shaped explosive. Anyone who makes the mistake of eating one of these is in for a nasty surprise.

name: Dracmon
description: Dracmon is the Dark Area's biggest prankster. It won't hesitate to risk life and limb if that means successfully pulling off a prank. One time, for instance, it nearly died when it decided to try to draw doodles on the faces of all Four Sovereign Digimon (whether it succeeded or not is unclear). While technically a vampiric Digimon, rumor has it that lately it's been so absorbed in pulling a prank on the Royal Knights that it's forgotten all about drinking blood. It's also said that anyone that looks directly into the Eye of Nightmares cast from the evil eyes on its palms are subject to its mind control.

name: Hagurumon
description: A mutant Machine Digimon shaped like a gear. There are also countless other gears built into its body that are constantly turning. If even one gear is removed, all of the others stop spinning and Hagurumon ceases to function. Hagurumon possesses the ability to infect foes with a computer virus that allows it to control them. Thus, Digimon of wicked intent often seek to exploit Hagurumon's powers. But since it lacks any sense of self, it has no way of knowing it's being used for evil. Its special move is Cog Crusher, which implants a black gear loaded with a computer virus into its opponent's body, causing them to go berserk.

name: DemiDevimon
description: A small Digimon resembling a bat. DemiDevimon serves as a familiar to higher-level Digimon like Devimon and Myotismon. Despite its low status, it's rumored to have been responsible for tempting Devimon, once an Angel Digimon, over to the Dark Side. What DemiDevimon lacks in attack power, it makes up for in malicious cunning, and it's always causing trouble somewhere. Fond of darkness and typically in the company of higher-level Digimon, it's rare to see it by itself. DemiDevimon's special move is Demi Darts, which throws giant syringes at the enemy to drain its blood.

name: FunBeemon
description: An Insectoid Digimon affiliated with the mysterious Royal Base, a secret floating honey base. While its daily life may differ from that of other Insectoid Digimon, FunBeemon has a cheery disposition and is a hard worker of considerable strength. It always gets along with Vegetation Digimon like Palmon or Lillymon. The Royal Base is under constant construction, and Funbeemon's mission requires it to collect field data such as flowers or plants a little at a time as building materials. It's therefore classified as having the Virus attribute. The base is also guarded by powerful Digimon that prevent any from drawing near, so the purpose of the construction remains a mystery. FunBeemon's special move is Gear Stinger, an attack that fires off a rapid volley of tiny, serrated stingers.

name: Betamon
description: An Amphibian Digimon that walks on four legs. Betamon is a docile Digimon with a mild temperament, although it doesn't hesitate to unleash its special move Electric Shock when angered, attacking its enemies with over a million volts of electric current.

name: Mushroomon
description: A small Vegetation Digimon in the shape of a poisonous mushroom. Tiny but potent poisonous mushroom bombs growing from Mushroomon's body cause all kinds of afflictions. Anyone hit by one of these bombs could start laughing uncontrollably, have their body go numb, lose their memory, or worse. Mushroomon is extremely ill-tempered and enjoys picking on the weak, but also has a shy side, always hiding half of its face. Its special move is Fungus Crusher, scattering multiple mini-mushroom bombs at once.

name: Armadillomon
description: A Mammal Digimon clad head-to-toe in a sturdy carapace. It is easy-going and courteous, but it sometimes pushes its luck. Armadillomon is a descendant of the same ancient species as Veemon, so it can perform a special Armor Digivolution. It uses its special move Diamond Shell to launch its curled-up body at the enemy.

name: Veemon
description: A new type of Digimon only recently discovered. Veemon is a surviving member of a species that once thrived in the dawn of the Digital World. This allows it to use Digi-Eggs to perform a type of pseudo-Digivolution known as Armor Digivolution. Of all its peers, Veemon is one of the best Combat Species. It possesses hidden power, and uses Armor Digivolution to bring out its explosive abilities. Though a troublemaker and a prankster by nature, Veemon also has a strong sense of justice. Its special move is Veemon Headbutt, which knocks down foes with a powerful blow with the top of its head.

name: Hawkmon
description: A calm, collected and extremely courteous Bird Digimon. Just like Veemon, it's a descendant of a unique species that prospered in ancient times, and can borrow the power of the Digi-Eggs for armored pseudo-Digivolution. Hawkmon uses its special move Feather Slash to throw the feather ornament on its head like a boomerang.

name: Wormmon
description: A Larva Digimon with a timid, cowardly personality. Wormmon is a descendant of the same ancient species as Veemon, so it can perform a special Armor Digivolution. Exceedingly weak on its own, Wormmon stands little chance against larger Digimon. But with the power of the Digi-Eggs, it can Armor Digivolve and display incredible power. Like a larva maturing into an adult, Wormmon will one day Digivolve into a Champion of great might. This Digimon is the very embodiment of future potential. It uses its special move Sticky Net to shoot viscous webs that bind the enemy.

name: Keramon
description: Keramon is a Rookie Digimon that Digivolved from Tsumemon. Now that its body has grown larger and its mouth is bigger, it can devour more data. Keramon is capable of consuming more than 100 megabytes per second, and most data is destroyed the instant Keramon accesses it. Extremely playful by nature, it thinks of its destructive acts as a kind of game. Its special move is Crazy Giggle, with which it unleashes a highly destructive beam of light from its mouth as it laughs—if you can call it laughing.

name: Aegiomon
description: A Deity Digimon with the upper body of a human and the lower body of a mountain goat. Aegiomon is usually affiliated with the same musical troupe as Sirenmon, reveling in the music by playing the Syrinx flute hanging from his waist. He loves peace, and although he dislikes fighting, an unknown quantity of power dwells within him, and he demonstrates exceptional combat prowess when fighting to protect something he cares about. Aegiomon plays Attract Echo on his Syrinx to draw the listener's attention, stealing its sense of self and making it unable to see anything but Aegiomon as it remains fixated on the tune. This gives other Digimon the chance to escape or pursue said listener. Aegiomon's special move is Stun Beat Blow, which strikes the opponent and discharges the electricity in Aegiomon's body through his arms, numbing the enemy's nerves and rendering it unable to move.

name: Ikkakumon
description: A Sea Beast Digimon discovered in a computer at an arctic research facility. Ikkakumon's thick pelt and sturdy body are made to withstand polar temperatures. The sharp horn growing from its head is made of Mithril, a rare metal, and the skin beneath its pelt is just as hard. Ikkakumon's clawed limbs are capable of emitting blistering heat at will. As a result, Ikkakumon can always maintain a firm foothold when walking on ice, even if unable to move quickly. In combat, Ikkakumon will threaten opponents with a bold roar, much like a lion's. Its special move is Harpoon Torpedo, with which it fires the horn on its head at the enemy, as the horn can be regrown.

name: Airdramon
description: A Mythical Beast Digimon with gigantic wings. Airdramon is an exceptionally valuable monster, thought to be near in stature to a god. It specializes in aerial combat, invoking storms with its roar and creating colossal whirlwinds by flapping its wings. Though quite vicious by nature, Airdramon is also very intelligent. Nevertheless, any average Tamer would find it nearly impossible to control. Airdramon beats its huge wings to unleash a cutting vacuum blade with its special move Spinning Needle.

name: Angemon
description: An Angel Digimon with six shining wings and a body clad in divine white cloth. This being of absolute goodness is said to bring happiness. Angemon remains utterly composed in the face of evil, attacking relentlessly until its foe is annihilated. Legend has it that Angemon has often descended at the head of a host of other Digimon of the same species when the Digital World was in crisis. It's also said that Devimon, who was lured to the Dark Side, was originally of the same species. Angemon's special move is Heaven's Knuckle, with which it pummels its foe with a shining fist of gold.

name: Kabuterimon
description: Even for a newly-discovered Digimon, Kabuterimon is highly unusual. Though it's unclear how it came to be an Insectoid type, it's understood to have the power of an ant and the defense system of a beetle. As you would expect from an insect, it only thinks about survival, and has no other intelligence whatsoever. Hostile toward Virus Digimon, Kabuterimon attacks on sight without mercy. Its head is made of metal, granting it impregnable defense. Its special move is Electro Shocker.

name: Gargomon
description: A Beast Man Digimon that is Digivolved from Terriermon, it's a special Hunter Digimon. Faster than its appearance suggests, Gargomon brings down its foes with unparalleled accuracy and precision. Its powerful legs let it jump high into the air, at which point it spreads its ears to glide. Cheerful by nature, Gargomon may lose control once angered. It's obsessed with its beloved "D-VI'S 503xx" jeans. It uses its special move Dumdum Uppercut to get close to the enemy and thrust up from below with its Gatling Arm.

name: Garurumon
description: A wolf-like Beast Digimon with a pale silver pelt. Garurumon's fur is said to be as hard as the legendary rare metal Mithril, and the blades extending from its shoulders are sharp enough to slice through anything they touch. Possessed of a physique honed in the frozen tundra and a fierce instinct for conflict, Garurumon is feared by other Digimon for its predatory agility and unerring accuracy in bringing down its prey. However, it's also incredibly intelligent and steadfastly loyal to any it acknowledges as its leader. Garurumon uses its special move Fox Fire to breathe out a stream of intense blue flames.

name: Ginryumon
description: A Beast Dragon Digimon with sturdy Japanese-style armor covering its whole body. Ginryumon is lighter than it appears, drifting gracefully through the air and fighting while parrying enemy attacks with its smooth and extremely tough armor. It has the courage to fend off enemy attacks with its own body, and the insight to accurately perceive said attacks right before they land. Ginryumon specializes in attacks with outstanding penetrative ability, and is unflinching in the face of any enemy Digimon. Because of the antiquated interface on its forehead, this Digimon is presumed to be the Digivolution of an experimental "Prototype Digimon." Ginryumon's special move is Metal Armor Blade, which impales its foe with an iron lance launched from its mouth.

name: Grizzlymon
description: Grizzlymon is a Beast Digimon that might seem ferocious thanks to its large frame, not to mention its deadly claws and fangs, but it has the honest and straightforward spirit of a true martial artist. It has the combat sense to match, too, relying not only on attacks but moving with a speed that belies its great bulk to avoid and deflect enemy strikes as well. Grizzlymon never starts a fight, but when angered it will draw itself up onto its hind legs and lash out with its heavyweight bear claws, "Kumazume." Grizzlymon's strength is such that just with this one strike it can critically injure most Digimon. Apparently, WaruMonzaemon wears its Bear Claw in imitation of this attack. Grizzlymon's greatest special move, Maul Attack, turns the force of an enemy's move against it, striking where it's vulnerable to defeat it in a single blow.

name: Greymon
description: A Dinosaur Digimon with skin hardened into a protective carapace around its skull. Aggressive by nature, Greymon uses its sharp claws and colossal horns as lethal weapons. Taming it earns you an intelligent ally of unmatched strength. Its special move is Mega Flame, with which it shoots searing flames from its mouth, incinerating all.

name: Coredramon (Blue)
description: Coredramon with blue bodies are said to have Digivolved from Dracomon that ate lots of Blue Diamante, a precious gem that can only be mined from mountainous regions with the highest of peaks. Coredramon (Blue) has developed strong wings to survive amid the steep slopes, and is capable of flying at great speed. Its special move is Blue Flare Breath, with which it breathes out scorching blue flames. Blue Flare Breath breaks down a foe's surface texture data, leaving the DigiCore of a Digimon hit by this move exposed and open to attack.

name: GeoGreymon
description: A unique Digimon thought to be a subspecies of Greymon. GeoGreymon sports a deadlier frame than ever, with the shell on its head as well as its entire body having developed into living weapons. It can charge up a Mega Flame in its mouth to maximize its destructive power and then unleash it as a Mega Burst.

name: Strikedramon
description: A "Commando Dragon" that seeks to become a Virus Buster. While Strikedramon still has many vestiges of Monodramon, such as the horn jutting out of the back of its head, it has so transformed its appearance into a Commando-Mode Digimon covered in metal plating that it now resembles a completely different species. Despite being an inherently kindhearted Digimon, should it happen upon a Virus-attribute type, Strikedramon becomes consumed by an instinct to exterminate and doesn't stop fighting until its opponent's data has been reduced to dust. It uses its special move Fang Strike to heat its metal plating to red-hot levels, turning itself into a mass of flame and tackling the opponent in a fearsome maneuver.

name: Snimon
description: An experimental Digimon built in a laboratory as a Virus Hunter. Made of praying mantis data, Snimon chases after its target with machine-like precision. Its cold personality makes it feared by both Vaccine and Data-attribute types alike. The scythes on Snimon's arms are sharpened to points, allowing this Digimon to cleave cleanly through anything. It has no eyes, but the red feelers on its head act as sensors to accurately track the target's position. Snimon's special move is Shadow Sickle, which unleashes a supersonic slash invisible to the naked eye.

name: ZubaEagermon
description: I am the Twentiest! I won't stop! I'll keep on running!

name: Sorcermon
description: A companion of Wizardmon from the other-dimensional Digital World of Witchelny. Sorcermon uses the magics of light and ice (advanced programming languages), and also has the ability to heal wounds with the holy power of prayer. Its special move is Crystal Cloud, with which it summons storm clouds from a wand topped with crystallized ice in order to cause a massive blizzard.

name: Gatomon
description: A Digimon brimming with curiosity who loves to pull pranks. Gatomon may be small, but it's still a rare Sacred Digimon whose appearance belies its true power. It wears its Holy Ring on its tail, proving that it's a Holy Digimon, although it will lose some of its power if it ever loses this ring. Besides the Holy Ring, to protect itself, Gatomon also wears gloves with long, sharp claws copied from the data of SaberLeomon. Gatomon's special move Lightning Paw uses its claws to attack the opponent.

name: Dobermon
description: Originally a Virus-attribute type, Dobermon is a Hunter Digimon that changed into a Vaccine type as a result of mutation. Like Snimon, however, it remains quite vicious despite its Vaccine status, living only to hunt down Virus Digimon. Dobermon is beyond the control of the average Tamer. Its special move is Grau Lärm, with which it lets out a howl that prevents its opponents from using their abilities.

name: Birdramon
description: A Giant Bird Digimon wreathed in blazing flames. Like Meramon, whose body is also shrouded in crimson flames, Birdramon is a Digimon formed from the Internet's defensive Firewall. Birdramon flies through the sky using its massive wings. Despite not having a combative nature, Birdramon nevertheless launches frenzied counterattacks in the face of enemy assaults. Birdramon's special move is Meteor Wing, flapping its wings to send feathers shooting down like meteors.

name: Firamon
description: A Beast Digimon known as the "Soaring Lion." Firamon is a helpful leader among Digimon that protects certain ruins in the Digital World. Its special move is Flame Dive, with which it envelops its body in flames and dive-bombs the enemy from the skies above.

name: Veedramon
description: A mythical Ancient Digimon that, even in the vast expanse of the Digital World, is said to have only existed on the Folder Continent. Veedramon is extremely valuable to Digimon Tamers and rarely encountered, even on the Folder Continent. It's said that only one Tamer has ever been able to win this Digimon over. Other than the V-shaped mark on its chest, for which it's named, not much is known about Veedramon or its surrounding ecosystem. It's sometimes mistaken for a dog for some reason. It has extraordinary attacking power for a Champion Digimon, exhibiting strength even outstripping that of an Ultimate when the chips are down. It uses its special move V-Nova Blast to shoot out a high-temperature heat ray from its mouth.

name: Buraimon
description: A Bird Man Digimon Digivolved through continuous training with the sword. This led to acquiring mastery over wielding two blades. Buraimon roams the Digital World to continue its training and also serves as a bodyguard, relying on its honed skills. Seemingly willing to take on any job for a reward, it's often treated as a thug. In reality, it's a gentle soul that never takes a job that hurts the weak. Buraimon's special move is Dual Swallow Reversal, a cross slash performed quickly with two swords to slice down a foe.

name: Peckmon
description: A Bird Digimon with powerful legs that runs faster than it can fly. Peckmon uses its special move Kunai Wing to hurl steel feathers it keeps under its wings.

name: Mojyamon
description: A hairy Rare Animal Digimon covered in a thick white coat. It lives in remote snowy regions, making sightings quite rare. In spite of the various reports of Mojyamon encounters, no evidence has confirmed its existence, and so for a long time this Digimon has been considered to be a mere fantasy. Mojyamon is a gentle creature that never shows any hostility, but even so, it treats its den and territory as sacred grounds, and doesn't forgive any who invade its holy land. It hurls a massive icicle formed instantly from water in the atmosphere with its special move Icicle Rod.

name: Frigimon
description: An Ice-Snow Digimon whose body is covered in snow and ice crystals. In spite of its chilly appearance, Frigimon actually has a warm and gentle personality. This Digimon calms the hearts of those who observe it through its sweet gestures and calm movements. Frigimon itself hates the idea of fighting, and is ill-suited to other Digimon who enjoy combat—Meramon in particular. It unleashes its special move Sub-Zero Ice Punch from its sizable frame.

name: Unimon
description: A Mythical Beast Digimon based on mythical creatures of legend, with the wings of Pegasus and the horn of a unicorn. It travels across the Net in the blink of an eye with the large wings on its back, and stabs foes with the sharp horn on its forehead. A "wild" Unimon is as hot-blooded as any untamed horse, but once trained, the Tamer can handle it with ease. Its special move is Holy Shot, which belches an energy bomb from its large mouth.

name: Raptordramon
description: An Android Digimon modeled after a feral Digimon with predatory instincts that enable it to reliably bring down prey. Raptordramon boasts an incredibly tough body as well as uncontrollable savagery, and so it has been remodeled with pure Chrondigizoid Metal of considerable weight to restrict its mobility. Nevertheless, it still possesses exceptional explosive power and flight capabilities, largely due to the feral Digimon it used to be prior to remodeling. Though small, Raptordramon is capable of taking down even ultra-large Digimon in a single blow if it can gradually unlock its abilities. It performs its special move Ambush Crunch by pouncing on the enemy and biting vitals with its sharp fangs.

name: Deputymon
description: A Mutant Digimon with a gun barrel for a body. Though the particulars of its genesis are completely unknown, Deputymon's sense of justice makes it an active member of the Virus Busters, special Digimon among Vaccine-attribute types with the ability to eradicate and delete the "evil" will of Virus Digimon. It also loves gambling—especially Russian roulette—and its fairness is beyond reproach, allowing even Virus Digimon to get away if they win at this game. Deputymon's special move is Justice Bullet, which transforms Deputymon itself into a gun that unleashes a justice-imbued round.

name: Leomon
description: This Beast Man Digimon is known as the "King of Beasts," and also the "Noble Hero." Standing out amidst the many savage Digimon out there, Leomon possesses both strength of will as well as a sense of justice, which it has wielded to defeat scores of villains. It has a rival in the "Digimon Hunter" Ogremon, which devotes itself entirely to acts of destruction. Leomon hones its formidable physique with daily training so that it can withstand all attacks, and it kills foes with its ultimate technique, the special move Fist of the Beast King. From Leomon's waist hangs Shishiou-maru, the Beast Sword with a will of its own.

name: Reppamon
description: A Digimon resembling a kamaitachi—a mythical weasel-like creature—with a blade for a tail. This tail moves with a will of its own, allowing Reppamon to handle even surprise attacks from the rear. That will doesn't always line up with Reppamon's, though, so this Digimon has been observed quarreling with its own tail during battle. Reppamon enjoys combat in wooded areas, making good use of its claws and tail to climb nimbly among the trees. Thus, one must exercise considerable caution when battling Reppamon in wooded areas. Its special move Rolling Tackle is a forward-rolling charge.

name: Icemon
description: A Digimon with a body made of ice. Icemon's origins are currently being researched. Perhaps it Digivolved from Gotsumon, or maybe it's some sort of mutation. Its special move Iceball Bomb involves throwing ice-cold frozen bombs at foes.

name: Wizardmon
description: A high-level Wizard Digimon from the Digital World of another dimension. In its home Digital World of Witchelny, it mastered the magics of fire and earth (advanced programming languages) and aims to become a great mage, but has first come to the Digimon World for training. Wizardmon is a little mischievous but also shy and always keeps its face hidden. Its special move is Thunder Cloud, which conjures up a storm cloud to launch a powerful lightning attack.

name: Witchmon
description: A Digimon resembling a witch, who pursued its rival, Wizardmon, from Witchelny, the Digital World of another dimension. Witchmon mastered the magics of wind and water (advanced programming languages) in its home dimension Witchelny, but then pursued Wizardmon to the Digital World and now trains vigorously in order to get a leg up on this rival that aims to become a great mage. Witchmon has a bit of a cruel streak, more than a bit of pride and loathes both convention and established routines. Witchmon's special move is Baluluna Gale, which unleashes a cutting wind imbued with magic power.

name: Gaogamon
description: This Beast Digimon is the result of Gaomon's physique developing and the claws that were once protected by gloves finally growing in properly. Although GaoGamon is a quadruped, its hind legs are strong enough for it to stand like a bear while it attacks. GaoGamon unleashes its special move Spiral Blow to shoot a powerful vortex of wind from its mouth in one breath.

name: Gawappamon
description: An Android Digimon born from the fusion of the data from a portable music player and that of the mythical "kappa" river creature. Gawappamon is almost always cheerful as it listens to its favorite tunes, but it also sometimes weeps if the disc on top of its head gets scratched. It uses its special move DJ Shooter to spin its disc at high speed and launch it at the enemy.

name: Kiwimon
description: A mysterious Ancient Digimon said to have been hunted to extinction due to the proliferation of the Internet. The wings of this Bird Digimon have completely degenerated, preventing it from taking flight. Kiwimon also bears some aspects of a Vegetation Digimon, with leaf-like objects growing from its head that it uses to absorb nutrients through photosynthesis. It has no way to defend itself aside from the hard shell covering its head, and its docile personality makes it an easy target. Kiwimon's special move is Pummel Peck, attacking with the ChibiKiwimon hidden in its body. The beaks of the ChibiKiwimon are just as hard as Kiwimon's, and they explode when struck. Even if this explosion chars them to a crisp, ChibiKiwimon will always bounce back.

name: Kyubimon
description: A Mysterious Beast Digimon in the shape of a giant fox with nine tails. Kyubimon is feared as a beast that brings destruction and decay, but in ancient times it was hailed as a bringer of peace. A Renamon with particularly strong abilities and a wide range of experience is said to Digivolve into a Kyubimon. This Digimon lacks attack power, but possesses incredible spiritual energy and specializes in spells. The blue flames burning on its four limbs apparently allow Kyubimon to gallop through the heavens. Its signature move Fox Tail Inferno creates and controls will-o'-the-wisps.

name: Clockmon
description: A guardian of time that governs computer timers. Clockmon manages all "time" and "space" on computers and across the Net, and can move time forward and backward freely between the years 1900 and 1999. It always maintains a neutral stance due to this incredibly dangerous and terrifying ability, refusing to take part in conflict between Vaccine and Virus Digimon. Many think that if Clockmon were to lean toward either side of this equilibrium, the Digital World itself would collapse. It uses its special move Chrono Breaker to destroy the very time that flows in the enemy's body.

name: Centarumon
description: A half-human, half-beast Digimon resembling a centaur. Centarumon's body is protected by a sturdy substance emitted from inside its body, and its right arm is fused with its weapon. It blows highly concentrated gas from the ducts sticking out of its back to move around at near-sonic speeds. It excels in attack, defense and speed. Pride means everything to Centarumon, and it hates being ordered or bound by anything with a passion. Its special move Hunting Cannon is fired from the cannon fused to its right arm. This attack is almost impossible to evade, but it consumes massive amounts of energy, so Centarumon avoids battles as much as it can.

name: Sunflowmon
description: A Vegetation Digimon resembling a sunflower. Sunflowmon gets a real energy boost when it's exposed to sunlight, which makes its attacks more powerful. On sunny days, it may even fly around by flapping the two leaves growing from its back. Its special move is Sunshine Beam, which releases a blast of sunlight from its petals.

name: Seadramon
description: An Aquatic Digimon with a serpentine body. When attacked, Seadramon will wrap its long body around the enemy and squeeze them until they suffocate. Fundamentally lacking any kind of intelligence, Seadramon swims through the Net Ocean wherever its instincts take it. Its special move is Ice Blast, with which it breathes out from its mouth at absolute zero, instantly freezing the water and blasting it at its opponent.

name: Coelamon
description: An Ancient Fish Digimon with tough skin and enormous claws. This Digimon is discovered in the Net Ocean whenever computer networks destroyed by malicious hackers are repaired. Coelamon's body composition is very primitive, with fins developed into limbs. Based on these facts, it's thought that primordial Digimon born in the Net Ocean underwent various evolutions in order to come onto land, growing more numerous and differentiating into various types in the process. Coelamon's special move is Fossil Bite, which attacks enemies with its massive claws.

name: Shellmon
description: A Digimon shaped like a hermit crab inhabiting the depths of the Net Ocean. Shellmon has a turtle-like appearance when inside its shell, but its body is actually soft like a mollusk. Its body gets bigger and bigger as it develops, and it switches dwellings each time until it's the size of a small mountain. Also, Shellmon has the custom of settling into anything it can push its whole body into. Its low intelligence and belligerent nature mean that anyone who encounters it needs to stay on guard. Its special move Hydro Blaster fires liquid at high pressure.

name: Starmon
description: A star-shaped Digimon discovered by chance in planetary analysis software at a space development center. Starmon is a space warrior with stellar armor, wearing gloves and boots emblazoned with stars. Its tattered yellow scarf speaks to the many battles it's survived, and its eyes burn with fighting spirit. Its eyes can even be used in a more advanced manner to hypnotize opponents. This hot-blooded Digimon has a fierce admiration for the brave Leomon. Starmon's special move Meteor Shower rains down small meteors upon the heads of its foes.

name: Tankmon
description: An Android Digimon resembling a tank. Known as the "Mercenary Digimon," Tankmon will back up Vaccine and Virus Digimon alike if there's profit to be made. It pulverizes incoming enemies to dust with its heavyweight power and the heavy ordnance covering its body. A conflict enthusiast, Tankmon heads in the direction of any strife that pops up. Wherever this lone wolf goes, conflict is sure to continue unceasingly. Tankmon's special move is Hyper Cannon, which launches a super-powerful missile from the gun barrel on its head.

name: MudFrigimon
description: A Digimon composed almost entirely of earth data. MudFrigimon is thought to be a mutant born from a mutation of Frigimon. It's friendly by nature and dislikes fighting, but when the chips are down, it can demonstrate rarely-seen power. It uses its special move Great Weight to put all of its weight behind a haymaker punch.

name: Dinohyumon
description: A Dragon Man Digimon resembling a humanoid lizard. Dinohyumon lives in an untamed land where every member of its fierce battle dragon tribe has the makings of a warrior. Its burly muscles allow it to swing its greatsword "Akinakes" with ease. Dinohyumon's special move is Lizard Dance, which employs dance-like movements to cleave through foes with Akinakes and the blades on its arms.

name: Tyrannomon
description: A Digimon that looks like an ancient dinosaur that existed in the prehistoric world. Tyrannomon mows down everything with its two powerful arms and massive tail. It possesses intelligence and a docile personality, however, and is easy to tame. This makes Tyrannomon a hot commodity among beginning Tamers, many of whom raise theirs with care. One could say it represents what Digimon are all about. It uses its special move Fire Breath to exhale flames the same color as its deep crimson body.

name: Turuiemon
description: A martial artist Digimon discovered in the hinterland of a mountainous Chinese province. Turuiemon has wandered the world in pursuit of its longstanding foes—viruses that exploit e-mail for malicious aims. It's blessed with exceptional potential as a martial artist, though it has yet to develop its skills. Turuiemon is a practitioner of Togaken, a fighting style of its own creation. Its special move is Gauntlet Claw, which involves a series of blows made with the Rabbit-Horned Iron Claws on both hands. This combo attack capitalizes on its rabbit-like agility and powerful high leaps.

name: Togemon
description: A Vegetation Digimon resembling a giant cactus. Its ability to store nutrient data inside its body allows it to survive for extended periods even in barren desert regions. As is obvious from its facial expression, it's usually impossible to tell what Togemon is thinking, since it spends most days staring blankly into space. But if provoked enough, its demeanor becomes violent and unhinged. Togemon's special move is Needle Spray, with which it hardens the needles on its fists and unleashes a flurry of punches.

name: Drimogemon
description: A Digimon that moves through the earth at high speeds with the giant drill on its nose. Drimogemon stays deep in the ground, so only a rare few ever meet it. It's docile and easily embarrassed, yet it enjoys a good prank, often taking Garurumon's favorite bone it buried in the ground and hiding it someplace else. Its special move Drill Spin attacks foes with its giant drill.

name: Dorugamon
description: A savage Beast Dragon Digimon possessing the temperament of both beast and dragon, this heavyweight creature makes most Digimon flee at the mere sight of its shadow. Dorugamon can be ferocious like a wild beast in battle, but the dragon intelligence at its disposal means it's usually quite docile. Because of the antiquated interface on its forehead, this Digimon is presumed to be the Digivolution of an experimental "Prototype Digimon." Dorugamon uses the special move Power Metal to shoot a large iron ball from its mouth and crush its foe.

name: BaoHuckmon
description: Huckmon went through strict training, refining an unparalleled combat sense and achieving mental, technical and physical strength in this form. BaoHuckmon continues to train while aiming for even greater heights, accumulating combat experience through countless battles against strong foes. The more this combat expert fights, the more it evolves. BaoHuckmon's desire to become a Royal Knight has only increased as it's grown. It doesn't allow others to determine its best course of action, believing it should observe and decide on an approach for itself. With its special move Fif Cross, BaoHuckmon cleaves its opponent with its sharp claws.

name: Blimpmon
description: A Vehicle-species Digimon similar to Mekanorimon, capable of leisurely flights through the sky. Blimpmon's soft balloon parts are protected by a metal coating, but it appears to still be under development, as its left flank remains exposed. Its signature move is Zeppelin Explosion, where it fires cannonballs from the two cannons on top.

name: Meramon
description: A Fire Digimon whose body is cloaked in crimson flames. Generated of the Firewall built to defend against illegal intrusions from the Internet, this Digimon has a violent temperament that reflects its blazing appearance and seeks to incinerate anything it touches. Its flames burn more intensely than those of its kindred on File Island, making it an extremely difficult Digimon to tame. But even if tamed, there's no telling when Meramon will turn on its master. Meramon uses its special move Burning Fist to cause its arms to flare up before punching its foe.

name: Monochromon
description: An Armored Dragon Digimon with a rhinoceros-like horn growing from its snout. When fully grown, this horn measures half of Monochromon's body length. The hard substance that covers its horns and half its body is as hard as diamond. They say there's nothing its horn can't pierce. Monochromon is known to excel at both offense and defense. Although it's herbivorous and comparatively docile, once it's angered, it will unleash fearsome counterattacks with its tank-like body. Its special move Volcanic Strike is a powerful flame projectile.

name: Lekismon
description: A Beast Man Digimon with astounding jumping capabilities that likes to toy with its foes using speedy movements. Lekismon's nature is as ephemeral as the phases of the moon, and its appearance is somewhat mystical. It uses its special move Moon Night Bomb to hurl hypnotic water bubbles generated from the Moon Gloves on its hands and put the enemy to sleep.

name: IceDevimon
description: A Dark Angel Digimon with a heart as cold as ice. This is the form that a Devimon with the cruelest spirit takes after Digivolution. IceDevimon deceives its foes with its silver tongue, then envelops them in wings of ice to freeze them.

name: Wendigomon
description: A brutal Beast Man Digimon formed when Lopmon underwent Dark Digivolution due to anger and hatred. Wendigomon isn't completely evil, and the kindness it had as Lopmon still resides somewhere deep in its heart. But the power of its rage overrides this kindness, making Wendigomon devote itself completely to destruction. In addition to its raw power, Wendigomon has the ability to manipulate time and space, and is able to warp by passing through other dimensions as well as create subdimensions of its own. Its special move is Howling Destroyer, which creates a shockwave capable of shattering even boulders.

name: Woodmon
description: A Vegetation Digimon resembling a great withered tree. Made of normal wood, Woodmon catches Digimon that pass by and absorbs their energy to survive. It can also use its root-like limbs to move. Brutal by nature, it attacks without rest when angered. Woodmon's sturdy wooden trunk boasts high defense, but it's extremely weak against flame and particularly Fire Digimon such as Meramon and Birdramon. It uses its special move Branch Drain to extend its branch-like appendages, pierce the opponent and absorb its energy.

name: Ogremon
description: A Digimon resembling an "oni," an ogre of Japanese folklore. The attacks from Ogremon's frighteningly well-developed muscles bring tremendous destructive power to bear. Extremely intelligent but just as temperamental, this rage-driven being wreaks all the havoc it can. Belligerent to a fault, it will boldly challenge even opponents with significantly higher battle strength compared to its own, and this has earned it the moniker of the "Digimon Hunter." The bone club Ogremon wields in its right hand was earned from defeating SkullGreymon in battle. It unleashes its special move Pummel Whack by swinging its massive arms.

name: Octomon
description: A Mollusk Digimon discovered in a virus that a malicious hacker used when trying to crash a rival's computer. Octomon is an obsessive collector, sporting claws at the ends of its tentacles that it obtained from Devidramon's data, and covering itself in Digi-Treasure that it scavenged from the depths of the Net Ocean. Many Fujitsumon, which are a small type of shellfish Digimon, have attached themselves to the pot that Octomon wears on its head. These Fujitsumon have highly-developed senses, and it's believed that they are part of a symbiotic relationship with Octomon, warning it when they sense danger. Octomon's special move, Spurting Ink, fires out a blast of highly-poisonous ink.

name: Guardromon
description: A Machine Digimon that protects computer network firewalls. Guardromon used to fight off anyone attempting to breach a firewall alongside "Net Keeper" Giromon, until malicious hackers infected it with a virus to make use of its impregnable defensive abilities. These hackers now use Guardromon to protect themselves from a certain Vaccine justice group. Since Guardromon's basic programming only involves commands to defend, it has no problem repelling invaders regardless of its new role. It uses its special move Destruction Grenade to pursue invaders to the ends of the earth and destroy them.

name: ShellNumemon
description: A Crustacean Digimon formed when a Numemon is smart enough to search out a shell to protect itself. This makes ShellNumemon slightly more intelligent than Numemon, but also much more skittish, causing it to flee into its shell at the slightest provocation. Its defense increases dramatically while inside its shell, allowing it to withstand kicks, stomps and the like. Its special move is Mature Poop, by which it hurls gobs of poop it's accumulated in its shell.

name: Growlmon
description: A Dark Dragon Digimon known as the "Deep Crimson Dragon." Having Digivolved into a wilder, more ferocious creature, the childishness from its time as Guilmon is now gone. Although it's a Virus Digimon, Growlmon may become loyal depending on how its Tamer raises it, perhapseven fighting for justice. Its roar is mighty enough to shake the ground, and Growlmon uses it as an aggressive display to intimidate the enemy before battle. It has the special move Exhaust Flame, which unleashes a powerful blast of fire with an explosive roar.

name: Kuwagamon
description: An Insectoid Digimon with giant pincers on its head. Like Kabuterimon, Kuwagamon possesses combat abilities far surpassing those of its kin inhabiting File Island. While Kuwagamon enjoys the protection of its strength and sturdy shell, it uses the power of its pincers to squeeze the life out of any foe it catches. It has a completely hostile relationship with the Vaccine-attribute Kabuterimon. It can use its special move Scissor Claw to easily cut through tough objects.

name: Gekomon
description: An Amphibian Digimon that mesmerizes those around it with a cry altogether too pleasant for its strange appearance. The chords Gekomon plays with the three holes at the end of its tongue and the improvisations created on the horn wrapped around its neck can control its opponent's feelings. Rumor has it that it's born when a hit song is created in composition software, making Gekomon a kind of status symbol among musicians the world over. Its special move Symphony Crusher destroys the enemy's insides with ultra-high frequency vibrations.

name: Geremon
description: A Mollusk Digimon of the same species as Numemon. Geremon lacks attack power but is unusually ferocious, rushing at the opponent no matter who they are. As expected, this obstinate creature gets taken out quickly, but then immediately forgets about its defeats. For this reason, it picks fights with formidable foes over and over again. Geremon uses its special move Hyper Smell to secrete a violent stench from its body.

name: Coredramon (Green)
description: Coredramon with green bodies are said to have Digivolved from Dracomon that ate lots of Green Malachite, a precious gem mined from forest regions thickly wooded with trees over 100 years old. Coredramon (Green) isn't skilled at flying, but has highly-developed leg muscles, and is capable of running at speeds seemingly impossible for a creature of its size. Its special move is Green Flare Breath, with which it breathes out scorching green flames. Green Flare Breath penetrates deep beneath surface texture data to damage the enemy's DigiCore directly.

name: GoldNumemon
description: A subspecies of Numemon whose entire body glitters gold, having incorporated data from gold mines into itself. GoldNumemon's special move is Goldurian Rush, by which it hurls a stream of golden poop.

name: Golemon
description: A Rock/Mineral Digimon discovered when performing digital analysis of an ancient curse.
