It has forbidden incantations in an archaic script signifying "plague," "curse" and "evil" inscribed on its back, apparently meant to safeguard it from the gas it emits. Approximately 90% of its body is composed of rock data, and it survives by binding up its limbs. An emotionless Digimon that doesn't act unless so ordered.

name: Cyclonemon
description: A one-eyed Dragon Man Digimon with an abnormally developed right arm. Once a brawny dragon warrior, Cyclonemon had its right eye crushed by the warrior Leomon, transforming it into a demon of revenge. It strengthens and grows its arm larger in order to defeat Leomon, and hunts for a chance at retribution. Shedding its pride as a warrior, Cyclonemon is now a maddened combatant who thinks only of slaughter, all for the sake of revenge. Its special move is Hyper Heat, which melts any and all things.

name: Sangloupmon
description: Sangloupmon is a bloodsucking wolf Digimon with a noble demeanor. It's one of the oldest species of Digimon, said to have survived since the dawn of the Digital World. Digimon who have their blood sucked by Sangloupmon have all the data drained from their DigiCores, causing them to perish, as they can no longer maintain vital functions. Sangloupmon is capable of teleporting to other locations instantly by disassembling its own data into packets and sending them across the Net. Its special move is Sticker Blade, which fires off a spray of thousands of minute blades to skewer opponents in the blink of an eye.

name: Sukamon
description: A nasty Digimon shaped like a glittering piece of golden poop. Sukamon was born from the accumulation and mutation of data scraps thrown away in the trash can of a computer desktop. It loves dark places, and being a pile of scrap data, it's just as disliked by other Digimon as Numemon. Sukamon's intelligence and attack power are both nonexistent. Its small rodent partner Chuumon can't fight, but is as crafty as they come, and always entices Sukamon into doing wicked deeds.

name: Tuskmon
description: A super heavy Dinosaur Digimon with giant horns growing from its shoulders. Tuskmon's foolhardy personality means it will charge at and destroy every obstacle in its path, earning it the nickname of the "Panzer Digimon." Specializing in charging tackles, Tuskmon has made countless Digimon fall before its attacks. The stars on its arms represent the number of Digimon that Tuskmon has defeated (one hundred per star). If its horns break, it can shed them like shark teeth and bring new horns from the back to the front, making any attempt to destroy its horns fruitless. Tuskmon's special move is Slamming Tusk, which unleashes a super dreadnought-class punch.

name: Devimon
description: A Dark Angel Digimon clothed in jet-black garb. Devimon was once a radiant Digimon of the Angemon species, but it became a Dark Angel when it fell into the distorted space of the Digital World known as the Dark Area. The prominent Mark of Evil on its chest is proof of this. Though it has a cunning and malevolent personality, Devimon is also extremely intelligent. It's said that any who stare into its glowing red eyes fall victim to its mind control and become subject to its whims. Devimon's special move is Death Claw, which uses its two extendable arms to pierce its opponent.

name: Deltamon
description: A Composite Digimon fused from three Digimon. Each existed as a separate Digimon, but a computer ran amok after getting hit by a powerful electromagnetic storm, bugging out and fusing them together into Deltamon. A Digimon with three heads and two tails, it specializes in three-stage attacks utilizing these physical features, making it capable of taking on three Digimon at once. Still, each part of it was once a fiendish Digimon, so while they share a mindset for destruction, they have no spirit of cooperation, and are usually on bad terms. Deltamon uses its special move Triple Forces to unleash energy from all three mouths in a single blast.

name: Dokugumon
description: A cursed Digimon in the shape of a spider, whose entire body is infested with a computer virus. Even though a Spider-species type, Dokugumon was originally a gentle and quiet Insectoid Digimon. One day, however, it was caught in a powerful electromagnetic storm, and was infected with a computer virus that had been lurking around the Net. From that moment on, it became one big lump of venom—in other words, a nasty computer virus, corroding everything it touched. Dokugumon's eight-legged mobility is worthy of special mention, too. Even if the enemy runs from it at full speed, this Digimon will be right on its heels, pursuing it until it tires itself out. And then, as soon as it stops to take a rest, Dokugumon uses Venom Blast on it, unleashing a dreadful, venomous attack from its fiendish fangs.

name: Nanimon
description: An unidentified Digimon that invaded from an other-dimensional Digital World. Nanimon went by the nickname of "Oyaji" in the other dimension, and was kept as a digital pet. It loves alcohol and violence, but once it invaded this Digital World (the details of which are still fuzzy), it Digivolved into an active creature. Inspired by the survival-of-the-fittest nature of the Digital World, it threw itself into battle. Its true power remains unknown. That being said, Nanimon has made it through many battles and evolved into its supreme form.

name: Numemon
description: A slug-like Mollusk Digimon. Fond of damp, dark environments, Numemon lacks both offensive power and intelligence. Any Digimon can become a Numemon if it isn't raised properly, but perhaps it has hidden depths? Then again, even its attacks are bottom-tier, flinging its own poop to defend against enemies.

name: Bakemon
description: A Ghost Digimon with a cloth draped over it. Bakemon is a wicked being born of darkness, and is said to instantly destroy the systems of any computers it possesses. What lies beneath the cloth is a complete mystery, and there are theories that the shadow cast under its body is a black hole. Bakemon lacks combat power and thus prefers not to attack its foes directly. Its special move Death Charm casts a powerful curse. Those lacking strong mental fortitude die in a matter of seconds under its effect.

name: Hyogamon
description: A species of Ogremon that lives in cold regions. Hyogamon is extremely territorial, flying off the handle and attacking anyone who takes even a step inside its domain (even getting into occasional clashes with Mojyamon over territory). Its special move is Snow Punch, which unleashes a chilling blow.

name: Fugamon
description: A Digimon resembling an "oni," an ogre of Japanese folklore. Fugamon is from the same clan as Ogremon, and shares its wild, battle-loving nature. Attacks unleashed from this Digimon's tremendous muscles hold terrible power, causing unadulterated destruction. Fugamon's special move is Evil Hurricane, which mows down everything with a swing of its bone club.

name: Flymon
description: A brutal Insectoid Digimon with massive wings. These wings allow Flymon to skirt through the air at ultrahigh speeds, creating sonic booms called "Howling Noise" in its wake that rob unlucky victims of their hearing. Its body is protected by a tough carapace, and it pinches foes with its huge talons before killing them with the extra-potent venomous stinger on its tail. The Digivolution process of Insectoid Digimon is still unknown, but from its face, some have surmised that Flymon originally Digivolved from a Kunemon-type creature. Its special move is Brown Stingers, which shoots a stinger from its tail that completely paralyzes the Digimon it pierces, turning it purple before ending its life. Incidentally, this nasty stinger can be regrown over and over again.

name: PlatinumSukamon
description: A Digimon of glittering platinum, shaped like a piece of poop. PlatinumSukamon is a type of Sukamon that has taken in rare metal data, giving it a gorgeous appearance but the same abilities as the original. It doesn't appear to have received any sort of power-up. PlatinumSukamon uses its special move Rare Metal Poop to hurl poop with a metallic sheen at the enemy.

name: BlackGatomon
description: A Virus Gatomon with striking black fur. BlackGatomon is the quintessential child of evil, spendings its days wandering through eerie darkness. An extremely rare mutation of Gatomon, very few are thought to exist. BlackGatomon is malicious and prideful and loves picking on the weak—all in all a problematic Digimon. As a Dark Digimon, it generally Digivolves into a Dark Angel Digimon. Just like Gatomon, BlackGatomon's special move is Lightning Paw.

name: Vegiemon
description: A Carnivorous Vegetation Digimon with long vines and a gaping maw. This fiendish brute emits a sweet smell from its mouth to lure in smaller Digimon, then ensnares them with its long, tentacle-like vines. Still, Vegiemon lacks any offensive power, making it no match for large-scale Digimon. When it grows, it will flower and bear fruit.

name: Minotarumon
description: A Dark Digimon possessing strong Dark Side Power. Minotarumon's movements are slow, but it has an extremely tough hide that leaves it unfazed by regular attacks. Its special move Darkside Quake uses the Demon Arm attached to its left arm to cause a massive earthquake. The attack sends shockwaves over a wide area, making escape impossible no matter how far enemies run.

name: Musyamon
description: An armored warrior Digimon that was once the data of a video game protagonist, but then Digivolved after being infected by a computer virus. Numerous battles with other Digimon have rendered Musyamon's appearance into that of a pathetic battlefield deserter, but that's only proof of its fearsome battle prowess and vitality. A savage warrior that's survived endless battles—that's Musyamon in a nutshell. The demon sword Shiratori-maru in its right hand is engraved with a forbidden spell that absorbs the life force of those it cuts, and is said to only grow sharper with every thousand Digimon it slashes down. Musyamon also has a special move called Kirisute Gomen that it unleashes from its Shiratori-maru. One day, it will settle things with Leomon, crossing its beloved blade with Leomon's.

name: Mekanorimon
description: A power suit Digimon used by other, small-sized Digimon, making it the first Vehicle-species Digimon in the Digital World. Mekanorimon is unique in that it can't operate itself, and fails to function unless piloted by other Digimon. Given its Virus attribute, the Digimon controlling it can also be considered a Virus Digimon. Mekanorimon is still in development, meaning its DigiCore will overheat if it's used too much. Its special move is Twinkle Beam, which fires a beam from the linear lens embedded in its torso. Any enemy hit by this beam loses control of their body.

name: Raremon
description: An Undead Digimon whose muscles have rotted off. Raremon tried to prolong its life by mechanizing itself, but the process was unstable, causing the data composing its body to start falling apart. Even so, its machine parts grant this creature life, preventing its death and allowing it to survive in this awful state. This crumbling form affords neither attack power nor intelligence, making Raremon act according to instinct alone. Its body emits a stench awful enough to send In-Training Digimon running, and it won't fight anything below Champion level.

name: Waspmon
description: An Android Digimon that guards the mysterious Royal Base, a secret floating honey base. The antennae on Waspmon's head have excellent scouting capabilities, and it constantly patrols in search of Digimon approaching the base, attacking any who even draw near. The propellers on its shoulders and stabilizer on its back let it move rapidly in all directions as it defends against approaching foes, driving them off with its powerful laser cannon. Waspmon's special move is Turbo Stinger, which fires its large-caliber laser cannon in a rapid burst.

name: Aquilamon
description: A Giant Bird Digimon with a pair of enormous horns on its head. Known as the "Great Eagle of the Desert," Aquilamon soars through the sky at Mach speed and can spot distant foes with its keen eyesight. Its horns display tremendous force when Aquilamon swoops down to ram into enemies. While many Bird Digimon are savagely brutal, Aquilamon values decorum and obeys those it pledges allegiance to without fail. It slams into foes from above with its special move Glide Horn.

name: Ankylomon
description: An Armored Dragon Digimon completely sheathed in hardened skin. Tough protuberances cover it all over, giving its charge attack incredible destructive power. Although as an herbivore it lacks ferocity, Ankylomon displays a brave nature nevertheless. It uses its special move Tail Hammer to ferociously beat the enemy with the iron ball on the tip of its tail. Any Digimon hit by this technique has its entire skeleton (or wireframe) utterly obliterated.

name: ExVeemon
description: A Mythical Dragon Digimon that gained Veemon's original power and Digivolved to Champion. ExVeemon is the pure breed of Veedramon, which is said to be a derivative species. Attacks with its developed arm and leg strength are capable of shattering a mountain of boulders without a trace. It's feared for this destructive power, but in truth it has a strong sense of justice, and doesn't use its might recklessly. ExVeemon's special move Vee Laser fires an energy beam from the X-shaped mark on its chest.

name: Guardromon (Gold)
description: Guarding a Chrondigizoit mine, Guardromon transformed itself to withstand merciless repeated raids by illegal miners. Guardromon (Gold)'s armor is said to be the result of taking in Chrondigizoit dust data floating in the air. This armor is more durable than a normal Guardromon's, and its special move Destruction Grenade succeeds in boasting slightly more output. On the other hand, Guardromon (Gold)'s armor is heavier, and this is the primary reason why its movements have dulled overall.

name: Stingmon
description: An extremely unusual Insectoid Digimon with a humanoid shape. Stingmon possesses both the hard exoskeleton and the simple movements characteristic of Insectoid Digimon. Excelling as an assassin, it prides itself on attacks that target vitals with agile movements and precise judgment, silencing the enemy with a single strike. Stingmon possesses a calm, cool and highly intelligent personality. It uses its fearsome special move Spiking Strike to skewer foes with the spikes on its arms.

name: Kurisarimon
description: Kurisarimon is a Champion Digimon that resembles a chrysalis. In order to Digivolve into a more powerful form, the Rookie Keramon temporarily enters a chrysalis state to store up its energy. As a result, it becomes completely unable to move, but its tough outer hide protects it while the tentacles that grow from its back allow it to attack foes. Keramon can sometimes Digivolve directly into an Ultimate Digimon without going through this Champion phase, but Digivolving into Kurisarimon allows it to reach a more powerful Ultimate form. Its special move Data Crusher involves using the tentacles that extend from its back to destroy an enemy's composition data.
